7 An Act relating to elections; amending 26 O.S. 2021,
Section 4-112, as amended by Section 18, Chapter 282,
8 O.S.L. 2022 (26 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section 4-112),
which relates to registration applications; requiring
9 all applications for voter registration to list a
recognized political party affiliation or an
10 Independent designation; directing applicants to
complete registration by selecting a party
11 affiliation or Independent status; and providing an
effective date.
12
13
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 26 O.S. 2021, Section 4-112, as
16 amended by Section 18, Chapter 282, O.S.L. 2022 (26 O.S. Supp. 2025,
17 Section 4-112), is amended to read as follows:
18 Section 4-112. A. The Secretary of the State Election Board
19 shall devise and distribute a registration application form to be
20 used for registering voters. Such registration application shall
21 contain the following information:
22 1. The applicant's full name and date of birth, county and
23 place of residence, and mailing address pursuant to the provisions
24 of subsection G of this section;
ENGR. H. B. NO. 3722 Page 1

1 2. A space or section to designate a political party recognized
2 by the laws of the State of Oklahoma with which the applicant
3 chooses to be affiliated;
4 3. The Oklahoma driver license or identification card number if
5 the applicant has been issued a current and valid driver license or
6 identification card by Service Oklahoma, or if the applicant does
7 not have a valid Oklahoma driver license or identification card, the
8 last four digits of the voter's Social Security number;
9 4. An oath of the eligibility of the applicant to become a
10 registered voter; and
11 5. Such other information as may be deemed necessary by the
12 Secretary to identify such applicant and to ascertain his or her
13 eligibility.
14 B. A voter registration application shall be signed by the
15 applicant in writing. The applicant shall personally subscribe his
16 or her name to or make his or her mark on the application, and no
17 agent, representative or employee of the applicant may sign or mark
18 on the applicant's behalf. The signature or mark must be the
19 original, handwritten signature, autograph or mark of the applicant.
20 No facsimile, reproduction, typewritten or other substitute
21 signature, autograph or mark will be valid. Notwithstanding any law
22 to the contrary, the Secretary of the State Election Board shall
23 prescribe procedures to authorize any person incapable of personally
24 making a mark to complete a voter registration application with
ENGR. H. B. NO. 3722 Page 2

1 assi stance of an official of any voter registration agency or
2 licensed operator specified in Sections 4-109.2 and 4-109.3 of this
3 title. Provided, for applications submitted electronically, in lieu
4 of the signature requirements set forth in this subsection, the
5 applicant shall consent to the use of his or her driver license or
6 identification card signature as provided in Section 4-109.4 of this
7 title.
8 C. Persons who do not indicate a recognized political party or
9 political organization on their registration application, or select
10 an Independent designation, shall be designated as Independents
11 deemed not to have completed their registration. Such applicant
12 shall be notified in the manner prescribed by law to complete the
13 application by selecting a party affiliation or Independent status
14 before the application can be accepted.
15 D. Any person may apply in writing to the Secretary of the
16 State Election Board for permission to print, copy or otherwise
17 prepare and distribute the registration applications designed by the
18 Secretary of the State Election Board. The Secretary may revoke any
19 such permission at any time.
20 E. All registration applications shall be distributed to the
21 public at no charge.
22 F. The Secretary also shall prescribe procedures to accept and
23 use the National Mail Voter Registration Form, or its successor, as
24 required by the National Voter Registration Act of 1993. Provided,
ENGR. H. B. NO. 3722 Page 3

1 to b e accepted as a valid voter registration application, the form
2 shall include the applicant's original, handwritten signature,
3 autograph or mark as described in subsection B of this section.
4 G. Applicants for voter registration or for change of voter
5 registration in any way shall provide a residence address and, if
6 different from the residence address, a mailing address. A
7 residence address shall include the street address of the residence,
8 including a full house number, street name or number, apartment or
9 suite number, if applicable, and zip code. If a street address is
10 not available for the residence, applicants shall provide such
11 information as the Secretary of the State Election Board deems
12 necessary for voter registration purposes. A post office box may
13 not be given as a residence address. A mailing address, which shall
14 include the city and zip ZIP code, may be the actual emergency
15 notification or 911 address on file in the local community, a rural
16 route and box number, a post office box number or a street address.
17 H. A full or partial Social Security number or driver license
18 number in a voter registration record or a voter registration
19 application shall not be considered a public record and shall be
20 kept confidential by the State Election Board and each county
21 election board.
22 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective January 1, 2027.
